FOMC minutes on Wednesday did not provide any surprising shift to this narrative.🧨Job Report Today🔦Today's job report is of great importance as economists expect around 268 000 new jobs added. Ironically  a slight miss on this expectation may be favourable for stocks as it could send a strong message on the potential of moderation in inflation. As we had discussed  essential commodities such as oil and copper have moderated by up to 20% in the past month  giving investors some relief that inflation might cool.💰Wage Growth- A Pivotal Point🏋Likewise  we need to see wage growth taming down as it can reduce the pace of price increases which in turn help the Fed to slow down the rate hike increase.
